                                           Created:     08 Jan 94
                                           Last update: 10 Jul 03
  
Disclaimer
==========
Avenir, the Utterdark domain, is the imaginative creation of its 
members and is not based upon any published work of fiction or 
fantasy. Nor are its roots in any of the AD&D worlds, though in 
fact we are told that it resembles some of them.

History
=======
Read ~Avenir/open/HISTORY for the thematic History of Avenir.

Area Projects
=============
Open
   Underdark: Five levels of tunnels running under Terel and into
              Avenir. Filled with creatures, darkness, etc.
   Fort: An outpost, protecting Sybarus from the creatures of underdark.
   Port: The main connection to the outside world.
   Sybarus: The City of Islands.
      City Island--first stage area of this fortified city is open, 
         beginning with the Bath.
      Bazaar Island--has bazaar/marketplace, dock, garden, pillory.
         Dancers of the Veil Club.
      Park Island--(Holm of the Icondit) recreational hunting 
         ground of the Shadow Elves with mutants as the prey. 
         Quests, bizarre animal and plant life.
      Dead Isle--Where corpses of the Faithful go. Populated by
         undead creatures.

In Progress:
      Bazaar Village: where everyone but the elves live.  A bustling
         community where the races live separately and harmoniously
         in service to the Gods.        
      Holm Expansion.

In Planning Stage
      City Island-- A fortified city consisting of greater and lesser 
         Houses, Houses of Lord Executioner, Lord Inquistor, and Lord
         Commisioner/Hegemon. Also, Zuggarat Pleasure Palace, temples,
         quests.
    
   
Guilds
======
Open
   Union of the Warriors of the Shadow: a fighter guild with ties
      to the Forbidden City.   

In Planning Stage
   Anchorite Priests: a layman clerical guild with a novel approach
       to spell libraries.
   Sybarite racial guild for all races of Avenir.

Abandoned, But May Be Returned To:
   Merchant guild: A combination of traders and mercenaries.
   Cenobite Priests: Very unusual occ/lay magic user guild.
